<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The abdomen of the type is missing. A small species (wingspan 9 mm). Externally 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. ejiciens" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ejiciens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. ejiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be separated from the other described Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a distinct whitish-ochreous streak along the fold from base to the end of cell, followed by whitish-ochreous spot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">The original description is quoted: &quot;Wingspan 9 mm ♀. Head, thorax rather dark purplish-fuscous. Palpi grey. Forewings rather dark purplish-fuscous; a whitish-ochreous streak along fold from base to beyond middle of wing; a roundish whitish-ochreous spot in disc at 0.75: cilia fuscous. Hindwings dark grey; cilia fuscous.&quot;</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Peru.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Male unknown. The type specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. ejiciens" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ejiciens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. ejiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the abdomen and does not have a genital preparation label. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clarke, JFG" journalOrPublisher="Dissertation, The Ohio State University" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/42780382" refId="B8" refString="Clarke, JFG, 1965. Catalogue of the Type Specimens of Microlepidoptera in the British Museum (Natural History) described by Edward Meyrick, Volume V: 1-581. Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History), London. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/42780382" title="Catalogue of the Type Specimens of Microlepidoptera in the British Museum (Natural History) described by Edward Meyrick, Volume V: 1 - 581. Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History), London." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/42780382" year="1965">Clarke (1965)</bibRefCitation>
reported &quot;The abdomen is missing.&quot;
</paragraph>
